<DOC><DOCNO> AP880702-0085 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-88 1219EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-MafiaArrests     07-02 0118</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Mafia Arrests,0120</SECOND><HEAD>Police Arrest 37 In Sweep On Calabrian Underworld</HEAD><NOTE>EDS: 'Ndrangheta is cq</NOTE><DATELINE>REGGIO DI CALABRIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police arrested 37 peopleSaturday in a sweep of organized crime gangs in the southern regionof Calabria.   The suspects, all charged with Mafia association, were arrestedfollowing an investigation by homicide and narcotics agents intoactivities of the 'Ndrangheta, the Calabrian version of the Mafia.   Police Chief Salvatore Patane said warrants were also issued for10 people already in jail. Eight other suspects remained at large,he said.   Authorities said the investigation focused on the warfarebetween rival 'Ndrangeta clans and their involvement in drugtrafficking, extortion and control of railroad and highwayconstruction contracts.</TEXT></DOC>